# Dashboard UX

The dashboard is **text-heavy today** and hard to scan. Default to **simple, intuitive flows** over inline documentation.

## Principles

1. **Task-first** — Lead with the action (form, picker, button). Help text is secondary.
2. **Progressive disclosure** — Presets and defaults first. Reference tables, cron syntax, and long explanations go behind expand/collapse, a link to docs, or a separate docs page.
3. **One primary path** — Avoid presenting equal-weight options that force reading. Guide the happy path. Advanced/custom modes are explicit opt-in.
4. **Less visible chrome** — Fewer headings, callouts, and paragraphs on screen at once. If a section needs a paragraph of context, consider whether the control label + placeholder is enough.
5. **Verify in browser** — Use [.cursor/skills/dashboard-browser-qa/SKILL.md](../skills/dashboard-browser-qa/SKILL.md). Credentials: `.secret/pockethost-io-login`. Base URL: `https://pockethost.lvh.me`.

## Prerender (static routes)

Root `+layout.ts` sets `prerender = true`. `(static)/` pages (login, marketing, docs, blog) are **prerendered at build time**. `(app)/` opts out via `+layout.ts`.

**Do not read request URL state during SSR/prerender** on `(static)/` pages:

- `$page.url.searchParams` / `page.url.searchParams`
- `$page.url.hash` / dynamic query-driven UI in reactive statements

`check:types` does **not** catch this. CI runs `pnpm --filter @pockethost/dashboard build`, which prerender-walks routes and fails with `Cannot access url.searchParams on a page with prerendering enabled`.

**Fix patterns** (pick one):

1. **Client-only read** (query banners, flash messages): guard with `browser` from `$app/environment`.
2. **`onMount`**: read `window.location.search` after hydration.
3. **Opt out of prerender**: `export const prerender = false` in the page or layout `+layout.ts` (token routes under `login/*/[token]/` already do this).

Before push/merge on `(static)/` edits, run `pnpm check:ci` (see [check-push skill](../skills/check-push/SKILL.md)).

## Styling

- Web Awesome (`wa-*`) + overrides in `src/lib/webawesome-overrides.css`. Do not put Tailwind border/bg/padding on `wa-*` hosts (see MEMORY.md Dashboard).
- Reuse existing patterns: `TabbedFeatureLayout`, `FeatureTab`, `QuickReference`, `AlertBar`, `wa-callout-*`, `wa-card-*`, grid form layouts.
- Prefer compact rows and aligned controls over stacked prose blocks.
- Error hints: one short line near the field, not a tutorial.
- **Required field markers:** Use an external `<label class="auth-label">` (or `.field-label`) plus `required` on the control. Do **not** put `required` on `wa-input`/`wa-select`/`wa-textarea` without also setting its `label` attribute — WA renders a stray asterisk on a separate line below your label. External-label forms rely on `authForm.css` / `webawesome-overrides.css` to hide the internal label row and show `*` inline on the external label via `:has()`. Prefer `wa-input label="…" required` when the WA built-in label is enough.

## Anti-patterns

- Full reference tables inline in forms (e.g. cron field legend on the same view as the picker)
- Duplicate docs content that already lives under `(static)/docs/`
- Multiple `wa-callout` blocks before the user can do anything
- Putting `PowerOffRequired` or API errors in `cta` instead of `FeatureTab` alerts / `powerOffAction`
- Adding explanatory `<h3>` + paragraph when the page title or breadcrumb already sets context
- `required` on `wa-input` / `wa-select` / `wa-textarea` with a separate external label (orphan asterisk on its own line)
- `$page.url.searchParams` (or `page.url.searchParams`) on `(static)/` pages without a `browser` guard or `onMount`

## Docs vs app

| `(static)/docs`, blog, prose | `(app)/` authenticated UI |
|------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Longer explanations OK | Minimal copy, maximum clarity |
| Tables and examples welcome | Pickers, presets, validation messages |

When improving a flow, ask: *What can the user do in under 10 seconds without reading a wall of text?*
